{{infobox person | name ='''Agustí Montal''' | Image = | Size = | Description = | birth_date = 1906 | birth_place = [[Barcelona]] | death_date = 1964 | death_place = | Cause death = | residence = | nationality = {{ESP}} | Other names = | Education = | alma_mater = | Occupation = | Years active = 1946-1952 | Employer = | Salary = | Assets = | height = | Weight = | Known = | Title = | Term = | Predecessor = | successor = [[Enric Martí Carreto]] | children = [[Agustí Montal i Costa]] | Parents = | Family = | Work = | awards = | Signature = | Web = | Notes = }} '''Agustí Montal i Galobart''' was a president of the [[FC Barcelona]] for the years 1946 to 1952. Born in [[Barcelona]] in 1906 and died in 1964.
After the [[Spanish Civil War]] and during the early years of the [[Dictatorship]] by [[Francisco Franco]], between 1939 and 1953, the president was appointed by the authorities of the regime. Montal's presidency began on 20 September 1946.<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.blaugranas.com/agustin_montal_i_galobart-itemap-118-2980-1.htm | title= blaugranas.com | accessdate= April 11, 2010 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150703190925/http://www.blaugranas.com/agustin_montal_i_galobart-itemap-118-2980-1.htm | archive-date= 2015-07-03 | dead-url= yes | df= }}</ref> But success came only in 1952, when the team under the command of [[Ferdinand Daucik]] during a season won five titles - La Liga, the Spanish Cup, Copa America, the [[Trofeo Martini Rossi]] and the [[Copa Eva Duarte]]. This resulted in a significant increase in the Barca fans, so he decided to buy land to build a new stadium - the [[Camp Nou]], since Les Corts was too small to accommodate a growing group of followers. On 16 July 1952 Montal resigned as chairman to be replaced by [[Enric Martí Carreto]].
His son [[Agustí Montal i Costa]] was also chairman of the 1966 Barcelona 1977.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.elperiodico.com/default.asp?idpublicacio_PK=46&idioma=CAS&idtipusrecurs_PK=7&idnoticia_PK=343728| title = elperiodico.com | accessdate= April 11, 2010 }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>
