'''Atlantique City Antiques & Collectibles Show''' was New Jersey's largest and longest running indoor antiques show.{{Citation needed|date=April 2008}} Founded in 1986, it is held in the [[Atlantic City Convention Center]], in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]]. {{Citation needed|date=January 2008}}
Atlantique City was founded as an [[antique toy]] show by Norman Schaut, a former New York advertising agency executive best known for the "Don’t Squeeze the [[Charmin]]" campaign.{{Citation needed|date=January 2008}}
More than 500 dealers set up at Atlantique City every March and October.
Krause Publications of [[Iola, Wisconsin]] purchased Atlantique City in 2001.{{Citation needed|date=January 2008}} The show is now owned by F+W Media, following the sale of Krause Publications in 2002.{{Citation needed|date=January 2008}}
In August 2009, F+W Media announced the cancellation of the show that had been scheduled for March 27–28, 2010.[http://www.collect.com/Categories/Article/CeramicsAndGlass/AtlantiqueCityShowCancelledC/L0]
